Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Quarter the @lime{1}(quartered).

Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and chopped into 2cm chunks) and discard the core and seeds.

Roughly chop the @parsley{10%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Place a large #pan over medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the pepper until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Drizzle in some @oil{to taste} (if required) then add the @ground cumin{2%sachet}, @paprika{2%sachet} and garlic. Fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @tomato paste{1%tin}, @prawns{180%g} and @dried orzo{170%g} and cook, stirring, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Pour @water{400%ml} into the pan along with @sugar{½%tsp}, @salt{½%tsp} (double all for 4p) and a knob of @?butter{to taste}.

Bring to the boil, cover and simmer until the orzo is al dente, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Stir every 3-4 mins or so to prevent sticking.

Once cooked, season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Stir half the chopped parsley through the orzo.

Divide your creamy orzo between #bowls{}.

Top with lime wedges for squeezing over.

Finish with a sprinkling of remaining chopped parsley.